                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 6 m5-001: The uninit keyword can only be used as the right-hand side of a mutable let binding (let mut). To fix this, either add the mut keyword to the let binding or provide a proper initialization value. Example: `let mut x: u64 = uninit;` is valid, but `let x: u64 = uninit;` is not."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/P0220",
              "id": "P0220",
              "name": "uninit only valid for let mut",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "uninit marker not allowed in immutable let binding"
              }
            },
