              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 4 m7-006: match expressions on enum types must cover every variant. Either add the missing variant arms or use a wildcard pattern `_` to catch the remainder. Diagnostic code lands in the type-system pattern region (0500-0899) — the issue spec's M0900 was out of M's reserved range (0300-0499); T0512 follows m1-003's T0511 reservation for the future borrowed-reference codepath."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/T0512",
              "id": "T0512",
              "name": "Non-exhaustive match",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "match arms do not cover every variant of the scrutinee's type"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 4 m9-004: impl coherence check. Each (trait, type) pair may have at most one impl block. Remove the duplicate impl or distinguish the type to avoid the conflict."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/T0513",
              "id": "T0513",
              "name": "Duplicate impl for trait-type pair",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "an impl block for the same (trait, type) pair already exists"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 4 m9-005: trait-bound resolution. At this call site, a method requires its type argument to implement a specific trait, but neither a generic-parameter bound nor a concrete impl satisfies this requirement. Either bind the type parameter to the required trait in the enclosing generic-parameter list, or provide a concrete impl for the type."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/T0514",
              "id": "T0514",
              "name": "Unsatisfied trait bound",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "no impl found for trait X on type Y at this call site"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 6 m3-001: record field layout computation supports u64 (8 bytes, align 8), u32 (4 bytes, align 4), u8 (1 byte, align 1), and pointer types *T (8 bytes, align 8). Records with fields outside this set cannot be finalised. Add support for additional field types in a future phase or refactor the record to use only the supported types."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/T0515",
              "id": "T0515",
              "name": "Unsupported record field type in Phase 6 layout computation",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "field type is not in {u64, u32, u8, *T} supported by Phase-6 layout finaliser"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 6 m3-002: EmitWalker field access lowering currently supports only the shape (*p).field where p is the function's first argument. Other patterns, such as nested dereferences (**p), non-argument pointers (local p), or more complex expressions, are not yet supported. Restructure your code to use field access on a dereferenced first argument, or defer support to a later phase."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/T0516",
              "id": "T0516",
              "name": "Field access only supports Deref(Var(arg0)) shape",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "(*p).field pattern required; nested dereferences or non-argument patterns not yet supported"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 6 m3-003: EmitWalker field-binding lowering assigns scratch registers in sequence: RAX(0), RCX(1), RDX(2), R8(8). The calling convention provides exactly 4 caller-save scratch registers. When more than 4 field bindings appear in a single function scope, the elaborator cannot assign a scratch register. Restructure your function to use fewer than 5 field bindings, or defer the assignment of later bindings to a later phase."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/T0517",
              "id": "T0517",
              "name": "Register pressure exceeded in Phase 6 field-bind",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "more than 4 in-flight field bindings in a single function"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 6 m3-004: EmitWalker RecordCons lowering currently supports only the cap-mint (4-field all-u64) shape when bound via let p : *T = construct_into(...). Other record shapes and binding patterns are not yet supported. Restructure your code to use the supported shape, or defer support to a later phase."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/T0518",
              "id": "T0518",
              "name": "RecordCons must be bound by construct_into(...) in Phase 6",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "unsupported RecordCons shape in Phase 6 m3-004"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 7 m1-001: both branches of an if-then-else expression must have the same type. The then branch has type T1 but the else branch has type T2. If you meant to discard the result, wrap in an action block { ... }; if you meant to use one branch's type, add an explicit type annotation or restructure the expression."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/T0519",
              "id": "T0519",
              "name": "If-expression branches have mismatched types",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "then and else branches of if-expression have incompatible types"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 7 m1-002 (PA7-004): when a break statement in a while loop provides a value, that value's type must match the expected result type of the loop expression. If the loop is used in a context requiring a specific return type, all break values must have that type. If you meant to discard the result, ensure all breaks are value-less or restructure the code to return unit type."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/T0520",
              "id": "T0520",
              "name": "Loop body type-incompatible with break value",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "break value type does not match loop result type"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 7 m1-003 (PA7-006): a function call argument has a type that does not match the expected parameter type. Ensure that all arguments to a function match their respective parameter types. Check type annotations in the function signature and verify that the argument values have compatible types."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/T0521",
              "id": "T0521",
              "name": "Argument type mismatch at call site",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "function argument type does not match expected type"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 7 m1-004 (PA7-007): a match expression on an enum-like u32 value requires an exhaustive set of patterns. Since the code generation uses compare-and-jump dispatch, the default arm (_) is mandatory to handle all unmatched cases. Add a default arm with `_ => <expr>` to make the match exhaustive."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/T0522",
              "id": "T0522",
              "name": "Match expression is non-exhaustive",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "match expression must have a default arm for all unmatched patterns"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 7 m1-004 (PA7-007): in a match expression, all arms (including the default) must produce values of the same type. If the first arm produces type T1 and a later arm produces type T2, the expression is ill-typed. Either unify the arm types by adding explicit conversions or restructure the match to ensure all paths have compatible types."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/T0523",
              "id": "T0523",
              "name": "Match arm type mismatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "all match arms must have the same type"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 7 m1-008 (PA7-008): break statements can only appear inside the body of a loop or while loop. A break outside any loop context is a control-flow error. Move the break statement inside the appropriate loop body or remove it if it is not needed."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/T0524",
              "id": "T0524",
              "name": "Break outside loop body",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "break can only appear inside a loop or while body"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 7 m1-008 (PA7-008): a while loop produces unit type () and cannot accept break values. Only infinite loops (loop { ... }) can return values via break. Either remove the value from the break statement, or restructure as a loop expression to return values."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/T0525",
              "id": "T0525",
              "name": "Break value in unit-typed loop",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "break value not allowed in unit-typed loop contexts"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 7 m2-001 (PA7C-m2-001): During IR traversal in emit_block_body, a RawInstruction child node was encountered but the instruction payload was not found in the InstructionSideTable. This indicates an internal compiler error: either the instruction was not properly registered during elaboration, or the side-table lookup failed. This is a structural invariant violation and should not occur in normal compilation."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/T0526",
              "id": "T0526",
              "name": "Instruction payload not found in side-table",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "RawInstruction node lacks corresponding instruction payload (internal compiler error)"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A binding declared as Linear or Ordered in the substructural lattice must be used exactly once. This binding was never used. A Linear binding represents a unique resource that must be consumed; Ordered adds ordering constraints. Check that the binding is referenced exactly once in its scope."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/S0900",
              "id": "S0900",
              "name": "Linear or Ordered binding never used",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "binding is never used (requires exactly one use)"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A binding declared as Linear or Ordered must be used exactly once. This binding was used multiple times. Linear bindings represent unique resources; Affine bindings may be used at most once; Unrestricted have no constraints."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/S0901",
              "id": "S0901",
              "name": "Linear or Ordered binding overused",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "binding used more than once (requires exactly one use)"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A linear binding from an outer scope is shadowed by a new let binding with the same name before the outer binding has been consumed (used exactly once). This creates a resource leak: the outer linear binding is no longer accessible within the inner scope and cannot be consumed. Move the outer binding's use before the shadowing let, or use a different name for the inner binding."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/S0902",
              "id": "S0902",
              "name": "Linear binding leaked via let shadowing",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "linear binding shadowed by let without consumption"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "An affine binding may be used at most once, but the analysis detects that it could be consumed in two or more sibling match arms (or if/then/else branches). Although only one branch executes dynamically, the static analysis tracks 'may consume' (not 'must consume'), so this is flagged as a static error. Restructure the code so the affine binding is used in only one branch, or assign it to an unrestricted binding first."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/S0904",
              "id": "S0904",
              "name": "Affine binding consumed in multiple match arms",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "affine binding may be consumed across sibling branches"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "An ordered binding declared in an enclosing scope is used out of declaration order within a handler body. Handler installations impose strict sequential-use constraints on ordered bindings: all uses must respect their declaration order. Reorder the uses in the handler body to match the order in which the bindings were declared."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/S0905",
              "id": "S0905",
              "name": "Ordered binding used out of order within handler",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "ordered resource used out of order across handler"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 4 m6-001: the borrow checker requires that a binding can be borrowed either as immutable (any number of times) or as mutable (exactly once), but not both simultaneously. This rule prevents data races and use-after-free patterns."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/S0906",
              "id": "S0906",
              "name": "Cannot borrow as mutable while also borrowed as immutable",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "a mutable borrow conflicts with an active immutable borrow"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 4 m6-001: a binding can have at most one active mutable borrow at a time. This prevents data races by guaranteeing exclusive access through the mutable reference."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/S0907",
              "id": "S0907",
              "name": "Cannot borrow as mutable more than once",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "a mutable borrow conflicts with another active mutable borrow"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 4 m6-002: the borrow checker requires that any borrowed value lives at least as long as the borrow. If the source goes out of scope before the borrow does, fire S0908."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/S0908",
              "id": "S0908",
              "name": "Borrowed value does not live long enough",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "the source binding's lifetime is shorter than the borrow's lifetime"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 4 m6-003: prevents mutation-through-borrow races. While a borrow is active, the source binding may not be assigned a new value."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/S0909",
              "id": "S0909",
              "name": "Cannot assign to value while borrowed",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "the binding is currently borrowed; assignment is forbidden until all borrows expire"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Per optimization-passes.md §1.2, peephole rewrites improve generated code quality. O1500 informs the user when a rewrite fired."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1500",
              "id": "O1500",
              "name": "Peephole rewrite applied",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "a peephole rewrite fired on the function"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Reserved for a future per-rewrite peephole diagnostic (currently O1500 covers the whole pass)."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1501",
              "id": "O1501",
              "name": "Reserved for future peephole sub-pass",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "reserved diagnostic slot"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Reserved for a future per-rewrite peephole diagnostic."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1502",
              "id": "O1502",
              "name": "Reserved for future peephole sub-pass",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "reserved diagnostic slot"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Per optimization-passes.md §2, instruction scheduling exploits ILP within basic blocks by hoisting higher-latency operations earlier."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1503",
              "id": "O1503",
              "name": "Instruction scheduling applied",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "instruction scheduling reordered independent instructions to hide latency"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Per optimization-passes.md §4, modern x86_64 CPUs fuse CMP+Jcc (or TEST+Jcc) pairs into a single µop, but only when both fit within one 16-byte fetch window. This pass aligns such pairs by inserting NOPs as needed."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1504",
              "id": "O1504",
              "name": "Macro-fusion alignment applied",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CMP+Jcc pair aligned within a 16-byte fetch window for macro fusion"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Per optimization-passes.md §5, basic-block-local dead-store elimination removes stores whose effects are immediately overwritten."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1505",
              "id": "O1505",
              "name": "Dead-store elimination applied",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "stores to memory subsequently overwritten without intervening reads were removed"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Per optimization-passes.md §6, picking the shortest legal encoding (32-bit ADD short form, Jcc rel8 over rel32) reduces code size and improves L1i density."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1506",
              "id": "O1506",
              "name": "REX/EVEX prefix tightening applied",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "instruction shortened to its smallest legal encoding"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Per optimization-passes.md §7, branch hints direct the code layout pass to place unlikely branches away from the fall-through path, improving cache density and reducing misprediction penalties."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1507",
              "id": "O1507",
              "name": "Branch-hint code layout applied",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "unlikely branches moved off fall-through for better code density"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Per optimization-passes.md §8, aligning function entries to cache-line boundaries (typically 64 bytes) reduces L1i cache conflicts and improves prefetching efficiency."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1508",
              "id": "O1508",
              "name": "Function-entry alignment applied",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "function entry aligned to improve L1i cache performance"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Per optimization-passes.md §9, constants appearing multiple times in a function are factored into a read-only constant pool, reducing instruction encoding size and improving cache density."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1509",
              "id": "O1509",
              "name": "Constant-pool emission applied",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "repeated 64-bit immediates factored into a constant pool"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Per OS-requirements §6 design-clarification 5: TCO ships in Phase 2 to support the kernel's exception-unwinder path. Capability boundaries, effect-handler installations, and ABI mismatches suppress TCO."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1510",
              "id": "O1510",
              "name": "Tail-call eliminated",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "final call + ret sequence rewritten as a jmp"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Per optimization-passes.md §10, loop unrolling replicates loop body by a compile-time constant factor to reduce branch penalties and improve ILP. Phase-2-m9-009 supports only known trip counts with divisible factors; remainder loops are deferred to phase-2-m9-010."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1511",
              "id": "O1511",
              "name": "Loop unrolling applied",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "loop unrolled by explicit factor"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Loop unrolling with #[unroll(n)] requires a known trip count divisible by n. This loop's trip count is symbolic or unknown, preventing safe unrolling. Remainder-loop dispatch to handle unknown trip counts is deferred to phase-2-m9-010. Provide a constant trip count or remove the #[unroll(n)] directive."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1512",
              "id": "O1512",
              "name": "Loop unrolling requested on unknown trip count",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "unroll directive ignored due to symbolic or unknown iteration count"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 5 m3-003: every mnemonic used inside an `unsafe { block: { ... } }` must be present in the MNEMONIC_TABLE. Unknown mnemonics could be typos OR could be valid x86_64 instructions not yet wired through paideia-as. The resolver tables cover Phase 3 m2-001's 10 base mnemonics plus Phase 5 m2-001's 20 privileged/system-ISA mnemonics, along with all Jcc condition codes, control/debug register moves, I/O port operations, and software interrupts (30+ total). Consult `crates/paideia-as-elaborator/src/unsafe_walker.rs` MNEMONIC_TABLE or file an issue to request additional instruction support."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/U1605",
              "id": "U1605",
              "name": "Unknown mnemonic in unsafe block",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "the mnemonic name is not in the resolver table; check spelling or file an issue if the instruction should be supported"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 5 m3-004: UnsafeWalker encountered an operand parsing error while elaborating a StmtInstruction inside an `unsafe { block: { ... } }`. This indicates a syntax error in the operand expression: invalid register name, malformed memory reference (e.g., '[rdi +]' with missing operand), type mismatch, or other shape error returned by m3-002's operand parser. The instruction is skipped; check the operand against the x86_64 addressing-mode rules in design/cpu/unsafe-blocks.md."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/U1606",
              "id": "U1606",
              "name": "Malformed operand in unsafe block",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "operand parsing failed; check operand syntax and memory-addressing mode"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 6 m1-005: cli, sti, hlt, nop, swapgs, cpuid, wrmsr, rdmsr, iret, iretq, sysret, rep_stosq take no operands. Source with operands for these mnemonics emits U1607 and proceeds with operands ignored (recovery posture for iteration)."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/U1607",
              "id": "U1607",
              "name": "Unexpected operands for zero-arity instruction",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "the instruction takes no operands; operands present in source are ignored"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 6 m3-005: A field access expression (*p.field) inside an unsafe { block: { ... } } references a field whose struct type has not been registered in the record layout table. This occurs when the target record type is not declared before the unsafe block, or the field name does not exist in the struct. The unsafe block requires C-ABI natural-alignment record layout information to resolve field byte offsets at parse time."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/U1608",
              "id": "U1608",
              "name": "Field offset not resolved in unsafe block",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "field offset cannot be resolved; declare struct before use"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 6 m4-002: A label with this name has already been declared in the current unsafe block. Labels must have unique names within the block's scope. Rename the duplicate label to a unique identifier or remove the duplicate declaration."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/U1609",
              "id": "U1609",
              "name": "Duplicate label declaration in unsafe block",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "label name already declared; each label must be unique within the unsafe block"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 6 m4-002: A jump instruction references a label that has not been declared in the current unsafe block. Either declare the label with a `label_name:` statement, or fix the spelling of the label reference. Label resolution is performed at parse time by the walker."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/U1610",
              "id": "U1610",
              "name": "Unknown label reference in unsafe block",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "label referenced but not declared; check spelling or add label declaration"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 6 m4-005: A bare-identifier symbol operand (e.g., `cap_alloc`) was used with a mnemonic that does not support symbol references. In Phase 6, only `call` and `jmp` (both conditional and unconditional) mnemonics support bare-identifier symbols in call position, which resolve to SymbolRef operands with PC-relative 32-bit relocations. Other mnemonics (mov, lea, etc.) require explicit syntax (e.g., `lea rax, [symbol]` for RIP-relative addressing). This restriction will be lifted in Phase 7+ with full symbol-address-of support. Either use call/jmp, or refactor to use supported addressing modes."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/U1611",
              "id": "U1611",
              "name": "SymbolRef operand not supported for mnemonic in Phase 6",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "bare-identifier symbol in call position is valid only for call/jmp mnemonics"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A symbol is marked as undefined (section_index=0xFFFFFFFF) in the symbol table, but no input PAX exports a symbol with the same BLAKE3 name hash. The linker cannot resolve this reference."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/B1700",
              "id": "B1700",
              "name": "Undefined symbol",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "undefined symbol — no exporting PAX provides it"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "An ImportsSection entry requests a capability (by BLAKE3 name hash), but no PAX's ExportsSection provides a capability with that hash. The linker cannot bind this required capability."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/B1701",
              "id": "B1701",
              "name": "Unbound capability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "unbound capability — no export matches an import"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 7 m1-001: when building an ELF object file, the elaboration phase produced no top-level function or object bindings to export. The resulting ELF would have no named symbols. Ensure the module contains at least one top-level `let` binding (e.g., `let _start : () -> () = fn () -> ...`) or other named definition."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/B1702",
              "id": "B1702",
              "name": "No exported symbols",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "no symbols to export in ELF output"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 7 m1-002: when emitting the ELF symbol table, one or more symbols violated layout invariants: (a) a symbol's range [st_value, st_value + st_size) exceeded its section's bounds, or (b) two symbols share the same name. Symbol names must be unique, and each symbol must fit within its containing section. This usually indicates a bug in the encoder or elaborator."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/B1703",
              "id": "B1703",
              "name": "Symbol layout invalid",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "symbol layout invalid (duplicate names or out-of-bounds ranges)"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 4 m5-005: region (lifetime) elision. When a function's output borrow lacks an explicit lifetime, the elision rules attempt to infer it from input lifetimes: (1) if a single input borrow has an elided lifetime, use it; (2) if a single input lifetime exists (explicit or elided), assign it to all elided outputs; (3) for methods, all output lifetimes take the receiver's lifetime. This warning fires when the rules encounter an ambiguous situation: either multiple input lifetimes (ambiguous which to choose) or zero input lifetimes but an elided output (nothing to infer from). Resolve by explicitly annotating the output lifetime with the desired region."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/L2001",
              "id": "L2001",
              "name": "Ambiguous lifetime elision",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "elision rules cannot determine output lifetime from input lifetimes"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Per OS-requirements §4 N1, a signing key is authorized for a specific set of effects (its scope). When signing a PAX, the PAX's effect set (from .paideia.effects section) must be a subset of the key's authorized scope. This error indicates a scope mismatch: the key cannot sign this artifact because it lacks authorization for some required effects. Check the key's scope and the artifact's effect declarations."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/Q0901",
              "id": "Q0901",
              "name": "Signing-key scope insufficient",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "the signing key's scope does not subsume the artifact's effect set"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 3 m6-002 documents this as the canonical hybrid-fallback shape. Operator opt-in is required via --opt-in-hybrid-fallback. See design/security/pq-trust-root.md (phase-3 appendix m6-005)."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/Q0902",
              "id": "Q0902",
              "name": "HSM does not support post-quantum signing",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "the configured HSM (YubiHSM2 ≤ firmware 2.6) supports Ed25519 in hardware but not ML-DSA-65; the PQ leg falls back to soft-HSM"
              }
            }
          ],
          "semanticVersion": "0.6.0",
